<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-02-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-02-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="205" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d205">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Calvo</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Costa Rica</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-02-13"><hi rend="italic">February 13,
                                    1896</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you, in
                            conformity with what I stated to you in person to-day, that the
                            Government of Costa Rica has observed with pleasure the attitude of the
                            Government of Washington in the Anglo-Venezuelan controversy as set
                            forth in the paragraphs of the respective communication, of which I
                            delivered a copy to you.</p>
                        <p>I avail, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">T. B. Calvo</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>